article.description: SF Austin smacks down Long Beach State, 74-45
article.headline: SF Austin smacks down Long Beach State, 74-45
article.linkText: SF Austin smacks down Long Beach State, 74-45
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Thomas Walkup and Jared Johnson each scored 16 points as Stephen F. Austin thrashed Long Beach State, 74-45 on Friday night. The Lumberjacks limited Long Beach State to just 16 of 37 shooting from the field (43.2 percent) on the road. The 49ers were 0 for 8 from distance and shot 56.5 percent from the line (13 of 23). Stephen F. Austin won the previous meeting with Long Beach State, 68-60 during the 2012-13 season. That game also was a BracketBusters pairing. The Lumberjacks (5-3) shot 49.1 percent from the field in the win, connecting on 26 of 53 shots, including 8 of 21 from long-range, and were 14 of 20 from the free-throw line. Branford Jones had 15 point off the bench for Long Beach State. The loss opened a string of six straight games on the road for the 49ers (5-5).
